Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Scaraboid
Description: Oblong plaque pierced longitudianally and engraved on both surfaces.  One side bears the name of Amun-Re with flowers above it. The other surface is inscribed with the name of Thutmosis III, Menkheperre, surrounded by a braided motif.
